WEBVTT

00:17.810 --> 00:20.354
-[ringing]
-[Boyd] Previously on From...

00:20.438 --> 00:22.106
All you fucking do

00:22.189 --> 00:26.986
is knock on our doors,
knock on our fucking windows!

00:27.069 --> 00:29.822
You wanna play games?
Come get me!

00:29.905 --> 00:32.491
[grunts]

00:32.575 --> 00:35.828
My blood is your blood now,
motherfucker.

00:35.911 --> 00:37.747
[screeches]

00:37.830 --> 00:39.957
You really did it.
You killed one of them.

00:44.003 --> 00:45.296
All this time, I thought

00:45.379 --> 00:47.047
the children were trying
to scare me, but...

00:47.131 --> 00:48.632
what if they're just
asking for my help?

00:48.716 --> 00:51.051
So Victor said his mother
wanted to rescue the children

00:51.135 --> 00:52.178
locked in the tower.

00:52.261 --> 00:54.096
I'm sorry. This is the only way.

00:54.180 --> 00:57.224
[screaming]

00:57.308 --> 00:58.893
Are you deaf?
I said, get the--

00:58.976 --> 01:00.478
Where did you get that?

01:00.561 --> 01:02.897
You're Victor's father.

01:02.980 --> 01:04.899
[Henry] My wife, Miranda,
started seeing things.

01:04.982 --> 01:06.901
She said it was like

01:06.984 --> 01:10.571
she'd been chosen
to free the children.

01:12.615 --> 01:14.492
-[screaming]
-[horn honks]

01:14.575 --> 01:17.119
But there's a town up ahead!

01:17.203 --> 01:18.537
You just need to keep
going forward! Please!

01:20.498 --> 01:21.916
-[screeches]
-[groans]

01:24.835 --> 01:26.212
Victor.

01:26.295 --> 01:28.589
I didn't know
how to get home.

01:30.633 --> 01:32.926
The Boy in White
was trying to tell Christopher

01:33.009 --> 01:34.386
that to save the children,

01:34.470 --> 01:36.472
he would have
to go through the tree.

01:36.555 --> 01:38.348
Christopher
wouldn't go through the tree,

01:38.432 --> 01:41.435
so I told my mother
what the Boy in White said.

01:41.519 --> 01:42.978
It was my fault.

01:43.062 --> 01:44.896
I was the reason
that she died.

01:44.979 --> 01:46.982
She was trying
to protect you.

01:47.066 --> 01:49.109
That's my job now.

01:49.193 --> 01:50.860
We thought you were dead.

01:50.945 --> 01:53.572
Your children
thought you were dead.

01:53.656 --> 01:55.533
You owe it to your kids
to be here now.

01:55.616 --> 01:58.828
This place wants us
to be scared.

01:58.911 --> 02:01.747
How we take care of each other
and how we always do our best,

02:01.831 --> 02:03.624
that's what matters.

02:03.707 --> 02:05.960
-You're not pregnant.
-I am pregnant!

02:06.043 --> 02:07.628
I can feel it!

02:07.711 --> 02:10.297
I'm not eating garbage
because I'm afraid!

02:10.381 --> 02:11.799
It's making me!

02:11.882 --> 02:15.302
Whatever is inside me,
it's getting stronger.

02:15.386 --> 02:18.472
Help me, Elgin.
I can save all of you.

02:18.556 --> 02:20.516
I can help you go back home.

02:20.599 --> 02:22.560
[Fatima] Elgin, please!

02:22.643 --> 02:25.896
Fatima's baby
is going to save all of us.

02:25.980 --> 02:27.481
He's not gonna
tell you where she is.

02:27.565 --> 02:30.276
You said that you weren't
gonna let this place break you.

02:32.069 --> 02:33.320
This place has won.

02:33.404 --> 02:36.781
[screaming]

02:36.866 --> 02:38.242
What the fuck are you doing?

02:38.325 --> 02:42.204
Boyd doesn't understand
how far he needs to go.

02:42.288 --> 02:44.707
-Sara--
-She's in the root cellar.

02:44.790 --> 02:47.334
[Boyd] I'm not gonna be
blindsided by this place again.

02:47.418 --> 02:49.587
I need to see it.

02:49.670 --> 02:51.714
[Fatima] Those things
that come out at night,

02:51.797 --> 02:55.175
they sacrificed their children,
because It promised them

02:55.259 --> 02:57.261
that they would live forever.

03:02.266 --> 03:05.144
[Jade] Miranda had visions
of this place.

03:05.227 --> 03:07.229
She's the only one who had
a connection to this place

03:07.313 --> 03:08.397
long before she arrived.

03:08.480 --> 03:10.065
It wasn't just Miranda.

03:10.149 --> 03:13.736
When I was a little girl,
I saw this place, too.

03:13.819 --> 03:18.365
[violin playing mournful tune]

03:18.449 --> 03:19.658
Anghkooey.

03:19.742 --> 03:21.160
Remember.

03:21.243 --> 03:22.870
Oh, God.

03:22.953 --> 03:25.331
The reason I felt
what Miranda felt

03:25.414 --> 03:28.000
is because I was Miranda.

03:28.083 --> 03:30.794
And Jade was Christopher.
We've come back

03:30.878 --> 03:33.839
over and over again because
we failed the first time.

03:33.923 --> 03:36.926
I need some time, honey.

03:37.009 --> 03:39.762
[Julie]
When I walked inside the ruins,

03:39.845 --> 03:41.639
suddenly,
I was in a chamber.

03:41.722 --> 03:42.640
[screaming]

03:42.723 --> 03:44.016
I think I was actually there.

03:44.099 --> 03:45.768
You're a Storywalker.

03:45.851 --> 03:47.686
Someone who can visit chapters

03:47.770 --> 03:49.021
of the story
that already happened.

03:49.103 --> 03:50.147
What?

03:50.230 --> 03:51.690
But you can't change them.

03:51.774 --> 03:53.651
Dad!
I think this is when it happens!

03:53.734 --> 03:55.194
-Slow down.
-No, no, listen to me!

03:55.277 --> 03:57.321
I need to change
the story, Dad, please!

03:57.404 --> 03:59.781
That was a hell of a song.

03:59.865 --> 04:01.992
This didn't have
to happen, you know.

04:02.076 --> 04:04.036
Knowledge comes with a cost.

04:04.119 --> 04:06.246
[choking]

04:06.330 --> 04:08.457
Your wife shouldn't
have dug that hole, Jim.

04:08.540 --> 04:09.708
[choking]

04:12.628 --> 04:14.588
No!

04:16.923 --> 04:18.926
[screaming]

04:20.469 --> 04:24.306
[sighs]
People are such fragile things.

04:24.390 --> 04:27.810
We have to stop
meeting like this.

04:27.893 --> 04:29.478
When did you
come from this time?

04:29.561 --> 04:30.854
[gasping]

04:30.938 --> 04:33.107
Didn't anyone tell ya?

04:33.190 --> 04:36.235
There's no way to change
a story once it's been told.

04:38.988 --> 04:40.364
[sighs]

04:46.870 --> 04:48.163
Just you and me now, Jim.

04:50.165 --> 04:54.461
I liked you. I really did.

04:54.545 --> 04:56.296
[whispered] Fuck you.

04:56.380 --> 04:59.633
[chuckles]
You always tried so hard.

05:01.135 --> 05:03.429
You carried so much.

05:04.763 --> 05:09.059
It's a terrible shame you won't
get to see what happens next.

05:09.143 --> 05:12.730
Because what happens next...

05:12.813 --> 05:14.982
is my favorite part.

05:16.650 --> 05:19.194
Would you like to know why?

05:19.278 --> 05:22.364
[chuckles]

05:22.448 --> 05:26.702
[ominous music]

05:38.297 --> 05:39.256
[sighs]

05:49.725 --> 05:54.480
["Que Sera, Sera (Whatever Will
Be, Will Be)" plays]

05:59.610 --> 06:04.406
♪ When I was just a little boy ♪

06:04.490 --> 06:06.825
♪ I asked my father ♪

06:06.909 --> 06:09.036
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

06:10.621 --> 06:12.915
♪ "Will I be handsome?" ♪

06:12.998 --> 06:15.417
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

06:15.501 --> 06:19.338
♪ Here's what he said to me ♪

06:19.421 --> 06:22.883
♪ Que sera sera ♪

06:23.634 --> 06:26.804
♪ Whatever will be will be ♪

06:28.472 --> 06:32.643
♪ The future's not ours to see ♪

06:32.726 --> 06:35.354
♪ Que sera sera ♪

06:37.773 --> 06:40.526
♪ What will be will be ♪

06:50.159 --> 06:54.915
♪ Now I have
children of my own ♪

06:54.998 --> 06:57.334
♪ They ask their father ♪

06:57.417 --> 07:01.004
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

07:01.088 --> 07:03.549
♪ "Will I be pretty?" ♪

07:03.632 --> 07:05.926
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

07:06.009 --> 07:09.847
♪ I tell them tenderly ♪

07:09.930 --> 07:12.474
♪ Que sera sera ♪

07:14.059 --> 07:18.230
♪ Whatever will be will be ♪

07:19.064 --> 07:23.068
♪ The future's not ours to see ♪

07:23.152 --> 07:26.238
♪ Que sera sera ♪

07:28.282 --> 07:31.618
♪ What will be will be ♪

07:33.120 --> 07:36.165
♪ Que sera sera ♪

07:50.345 --> 07:53.015
What do you mean, they
sacrificed their children?

07:53.098 --> 07:55.058
[breathing heavily]

07:55.142 --> 07:59.688
Those things in the woods.
They were people once.

07:59.771 --> 08:02.149
They made a--

08:02.232 --> 08:07.112
a bargain
with something horrible.

08:07.196 --> 08:09.239
But I didn't see--

08:09.323 --> 08:10.657
I-I couldn't see it. I--

08:10.741 --> 08:13.577
[Ellis] It's okay.
It's okay. Hey.

08:13.660 --> 08:15.204
-[screams]
-[Ellis] Hey.

08:15.287 --> 08:16.955
Hey, hey, hey.
You're okay. You're okay.

08:17.039 --> 08:18.165
We gotta get her out of here.

08:18.248 --> 08:19.625
Baby,
we gotta go, all right?

08:19.707 --> 08:21.460
No. Boyd was here.
Where's Boyd?

08:21.543 --> 08:23.962
-I'll find him. Go! Come on.
-We can't leave without him.

08:24.046 --> 08:25.547
Fatima,
we have to go! Come on.

08:25.631 --> 08:27.007
-Ellis!
-Please.

08:27.090 --> 08:28.300
-No. I'm okay. I can--
-Hey.

08:28.383 --> 08:30.677
-[shouts in pain]
-Hey! Help me. Hey! Hey!

08:30.761 --> 08:33.388
-[shouts in pain]
-I know, I know.

08:33.472 --> 08:36.225
Hey, you're okay.
Come on. Kenny.

08:36.308 --> 08:38.101
But we can't--

08:38.184 --> 08:40.729
He's gonna be okay.
He's gonna be okay.

08:40.812 --> 08:42.773
-Come on, baby.
-All right?

08:42.856 --> 08:45.108
We gotta go.
We gotta go.

08:45.192 --> 08:47.444
We're gonna be okay.
Come on.

08:47.527 --> 08:50.030
It's okay.
Come on. I got you.

08:50.113 --> 08:54.409
[Fatima breathing shakily]

08:54.493 --> 08:55.369
[Ellis] I got you.

08:58.664 --> 08:59.748
You good?

08:59.831 --> 09:02.751
-Yeah.
-Okay, come on. Let's go.

09:02.834 --> 09:07.005
[wood creaking]

09:12.261 --> 09:16.098
[suspenseful music]

09:22.688 --> 09:23.814
Boyd?

09:44.751 --> 09:45.877
Boyd!

09:58.432 --> 09:59.558
[whispering] Boyd?

10:21.204 --> 10:25.417
Shh-shh-shh-shh-shh.

10:25.500 --> 10:27.586
Hey. Hey. Shh.

10:27.669 --> 10:30.172
We gotta get outta here.
Okay?

10:30.255 --> 10:31.214
Okay.

10:31.298 --> 10:32.674
We gotta go that way.

10:35.093 --> 10:36.303
Hello, Kenny.

10:38.597 --> 10:40.724
It's nice to see you again.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.434
-No.
-[Boyd] Move, move!

10:42.517 --> 10:44.227
Now! Move! Go, go!

10:46.229 --> 10:47.981
[breathing heavily]

10:48.065 --> 10:49.858
Keep going!
Keep going! Move it!

10:49.941 --> 10:52.277
We got it! Keep going!

10:52.361 --> 10:54.780
Come on!
Hurry up.

10:54.863 --> 10:56.573
Watch out!

10:56.656 --> 10:58.200
What the fuck?!

10:58.283 --> 11:00.285
How?! He didn't--

11:00.369 --> 11:01.870
-I know.
-We-- We burned him!

11:01.953 --> 11:03.288
-I know.
-We fucking burned him!

11:03.372 --> 11:05.332
I know! I know!

11:05.415 --> 11:07.167
My God. How did--
how did he even get--

11:07.250 --> 11:08.168
The baby.

11:09.336 --> 11:10.670
What?

11:10.754 --> 11:12.839
The baby.

11:12.923 --> 11:15.050
I watched it grow.

11:15.133 --> 11:17.344
I watched it stand up...

11:17.427 --> 11:19.304
and smile.

11:21.264 --> 11:25.435
You're-- you're telling me that
Fatima gave birth to that thing?

11:25.519 --> 11:27.562
Is that what you're saying?

11:29.648 --> 11:30.857
Yeah.

11:34.694 --> 11:36.655
-[Donna] You good?
-Yeah, I'm fine. Can you just--

11:36.738 --> 11:38.573
Can you just please
tell me what's going on?

11:38.657 --> 11:40.617
-I will.
-Donna!

11:44.204 --> 11:46.039
Any word from Boyd yet?

11:47.540 --> 11:50.335
[voices chattering]

11:50.419 --> 11:51.795
People are starting
to come back.

11:51.878 --> 11:54.589
[footsteps thudding]

11:54.673 --> 11:57.968
-I should go.
-Yeah.

11:58.051 --> 11:59.469
That's probably best.

12:06.601 --> 12:07.727
Donna,
what the fuck is going on?

12:07.811 --> 12:09.062
In here.

12:11.731 --> 12:13.483
[whimpering]

12:15.235 --> 12:16.611
[door opens]

12:16.695 --> 12:18.447
Jesus.

12:18.530 --> 12:21.366
Hey. Put that down.

12:21.450 --> 12:23.118
She's here to help.

12:23.201 --> 12:24.661
Oh, come--
For fuck's sake,

12:24.744 --> 12:27.581
we all know it's not loaded!
Just put it away.

12:30.417 --> 12:33.336
Now go. You got
nothing else to do here.

12:39.009 --> 12:40.594
Fine. Then stay.

12:43.096 --> 12:44.014
[sighs]

12:44.097 --> 12:45.765
Elgin.

12:45.849 --> 12:47.350
Elgin?

12:47.434 --> 12:48.894
Kristi's here to help you.

12:48.977 --> 12:50.437
Can you hear me?

12:50.520 --> 12:53.106
I need you
to roll over. Okay?

12:53.190 --> 12:55.317
Come on. Come on.

12:55.400 --> 12:58.487
-Just careful. Okay.
-There. Come on.

12:58.570 --> 13:01.281
Okay, now's the part where
you tell me what happened.

13:01.364 --> 13:03.575
Sara took his eye out
with a screwdriver.

13:05.327 --> 13:06.953
She had reasons.

13:07.037 --> 13:09.039
-Can you get me a chair?
-Yeah.

13:09.122 --> 13:09.998
Okay.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.043
Okay.

13:13.126 --> 13:14.669
Thank you.

13:16.171 --> 13:19.549
Okay, Elgin, can you take
your hand away?

13:19.633 --> 13:20.926
It's okay.

13:24.596 --> 13:26.056
[exhales]

13:26.139 --> 13:27.933
[Donna]
Can you stitch him up?

13:29.768 --> 13:32.270
Yeah, I can do my best.

13:32.354 --> 13:33.563
Donna, why--

13:33.647 --> 13:35.023
-Let's talk later.
-[Clara] Donna?

13:35.106 --> 13:36.107
Yes! Just hold on, Clara!

13:36.191 --> 13:37.442
Fatima's back.

13:37.526 --> 13:38.735
She and Ellis
are coming up the hill.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.028
-Okay, okay.
-What happened?

13:40.111 --> 13:41.821
No, nothing! Nothing!
Back out!

13:41.905 --> 13:43.782
-Can I get some ice?
-Yeah. Go!

13:48.995 --> 13:53.250
[eerie music]

13:58.797 --> 14:00.840
[exhales]

14:13.478 --> 14:15.230
Yeah.

14:17.941 --> 14:22.237
[ominous music]

14:22.320 --> 14:29.202
♪

14:42.299 --> 14:45.719
Boyd! What--

14:45.802 --> 14:47.387
What--

14:47.470 --> 14:49.764
Boyd, what are we doing?

14:49.848 --> 14:52.058
Shouldn't... we...

14:55.020 --> 14:56.479
[Kenny]
What the fuck is that?

14:59.816 --> 15:01.192
What--

15:01.276 --> 15:04.362
What is it?
What-- Boyd!

15:12.996 --> 15:13.872
Wh--

15:18.168 --> 15:19.586
Okay.

15:19.669 --> 15:21.296
Boyd.

15:22.922 --> 15:24.174
Boyd, what the fuck
are you doing?!

15:25.634 --> 15:27.010
[exhales heavily]

15:27.093 --> 15:30.221
This is every bullet
that we have,

15:30.305 --> 15:33.224
taken from every gun that's
ever come through here.

15:33.308 --> 15:37.520
I just need to make sure--
I just need to make sure

15:37.604 --> 15:40.523
that if push comes to shove,
we have enough.

15:40.607 --> 15:41.691
Enough for what?

15:43.401 --> 15:44.903
Between Colony House and town,

15:44.986 --> 15:46.655
how many people
we got here right now?

15:47.614 --> 15:49.741
I'm gonna need
a headcount. Thanks.

15:49.824 --> 15:51.159
'Kay, whatever it is that
you're doing right now,

15:51.242 --> 15:52.118
you need to stop.

15:53.912 --> 15:55.455
Boyd, you need--
you need to stop!

15:55.538 --> 15:58.792
Hey! We had one win, Kenny!

15:58.875 --> 16:02.212
One goddamn victory,

16:02.295 --> 16:04.756
and even that, we couldn't
get one motherfuckin'...

16:04.839 --> 16:06.091
Okay.

16:07.967 --> 16:10.970
What we just saw down there,
that means

16:11.054 --> 16:13.848
there is no way to fight back
against those things.

16:13.932 --> 16:18.144
There is no way,
none, to win.

16:20.021 --> 16:21.981
The day may come when
the only thing we get to decide

16:22.065 --> 16:25.402
is how we choose to leave.

16:25.485 --> 16:26.903
We can either let
those things down there

16:26.986 --> 16:28.738
rip us to fuckin' pieces

16:28.822 --> 16:30.073
or...

16:32.575 --> 16:33.743
Or...

16:36.037 --> 16:37.122
Right.

16:41.918 --> 16:44.963
I just...

16:45.046 --> 16:48.758
need to make sure
there's enough,

16:48.842 --> 16:50.009
just in case.

16:53.847 --> 16:54.973
Kenny, please.

16:55.056 --> 16:56.057
All right.

16:56.141 --> 16:57.058
Please.

16:57.142 --> 16:58.017
Yep.

17:04.357 --> 17:05.942
Forty-seven.

17:07.152 --> 17:08.027
What?

17:13.950 --> 17:17.787
I did a count when we were
doing interviews about Tillie.

17:22.208 --> 17:25.170
We have 47 people.

17:29.340 --> 17:30.592
Forty-seven.

17:34.387 --> 17:36.306
Okay.
Let's take the ice away.

17:46.524 --> 17:49.110
You must think
I'm a pretty awful person.

17:49.194 --> 17:51.613
I might have
at one point, yeah.

17:51.696 --> 17:53.031
And now?

17:54.240 --> 17:57.494
Now I think this place does
bad things to good people.

17:58.870 --> 18:01.915
Okay. I'm just gonna numb
your eye with the spray, okay?

18:01.998 --> 18:03.583
It's gonna feel a bit wet.

18:03.666 --> 18:05.960
It's okay.

18:06.044 --> 18:07.754
[winces]

18:07.837 --> 18:08.755
Uh, hey.

18:09.923 --> 18:11.508
Can I get your help?

18:11.591 --> 18:12.884
Yeah.

18:12.967 --> 18:14.427
I just need you
to hold his head still.

18:14.511 --> 18:15.470
I'm here.

18:15.553 --> 18:16.930
Okay. Put these on.

18:20.892 --> 18:23.144
Can you feel this?

18:23.228 --> 18:24.187
Yeah?

18:24.270 --> 18:25.313
-Yeah.
-Okay.

18:25.396 --> 18:26.773
Give it a little bit longer.

18:26.856 --> 18:28.608
Okay. So, just hold
his neck really still.

18:28.691 --> 18:29.818
Like this?

18:29.901 --> 18:31.110
-Yeah, like that.
-Right there?

18:31.194 --> 18:32.654
-Then tilt it back.
-I got you.

18:32.737 --> 18:35.281
Once the baby was born,
we were supposed to go home.

18:35.365 --> 18:38.284
If Fatima's back,
maybe that means it's done.

18:38.368 --> 18:40.620
Maybe it's-- maybe it's
still gonna work out.

18:40.703 --> 18:44.916
Look, Elgin,
something here lied to you.

18:44.999 --> 18:47.377
You're not the first
person it's happened to,

18:47.460 --> 18:49.796
and you probably
won't be the last.

18:49.879 --> 18:52.924
There's no version of any
of this working out.

18:53.007 --> 18:54.884
All right.
You ready to go?

18:54.968 --> 18:57.345
I'm gonna go as fast
as I can, all right?

18:57.428 --> 19:00.056
Deep breath, deep breath.
Here, hold this.

19:00.139 --> 19:01.349
I got you. I got you.

19:01.432 --> 19:03.101
Hold this, Elgin. Here.

19:03.184 --> 19:06.271
Squeeze it nice and tight,
okay? Here we go.

19:06.354 --> 19:07.272
Okay.

19:10.400 --> 19:11.568
[gasping]

19:11.651 --> 19:14.070
[breathing shakily]

19:14.153 --> 19:16.406
[whimpering]

19:16.489 --> 19:18.825
[whimpering]

19:18.908 --> 19:22.412
Ah...
[whimpering]

19:22.495 --> 19:26.624
[whimpering]

19:26.708 --> 19:28.501
Okay.
You're doing great.

19:28.585 --> 19:30.003
Okay, one more.

19:30.086 --> 19:31.504
You're doing great.
Just breathe.

19:31.588 --> 19:33.131
-Okay.
-It's okay.

19:36.134 --> 19:38.094
Okay. Steady again, okay?

19:38.177 --> 19:39.137
[Acosta] Okay, got it.

19:39.220 --> 19:40.597
Good.

19:40.680 --> 19:42.932
It's okay. We got you.
I got you. I got you.

19:43.016 --> 19:44.893
You're doing great.
You're doing great.

19:44.976 --> 19:46.269
[crying out]

19:46.352 --> 19:50.231
[ominous music]

20:10.418 --> 20:11.878
[door opens]

20:13.755 --> 20:14.631
Mom!

20:18.801 --> 20:19.886
Hey, buddy.

20:22.305 --> 20:23.222
Hey.

20:24.641 --> 20:26.643
Where's your father?

20:26.726 --> 20:27.936
He's not back yet.

20:29.395 --> 20:30.980
Wasn't he with you?

20:31.064 --> 20:33.775
Yeah, yeah, no, he was.
Uh, we just got separated. I...

20:33.858 --> 20:35.401
What's wrong?

20:36.653 --> 20:37.946
Nothing.

20:38.029 --> 20:39.697
Nothing, honey.
Let's-- Let's go home.

20:40.990 --> 20:41.866
[tires screeching]

20:41.950 --> 20:44.327
[tires screeching]

20:44.410 --> 20:46.412
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

20:48.998 --> 20:50.708
-[engine revving]
-[indistinct yelling]

20:50.792 --> 20:53.670
-The fuck?
-[man] Watch out!

20:53.753 --> 20:56.005
-[engine revving]
-Hey!

21:02.053 --> 21:02.971
[cries out]

21:08.267 --> 21:09.769
Okay,
stay with your sister.

21:09.852 --> 21:10.812
Why?

21:10.895 --> 21:12.313
Just stay here.

21:13.398 --> 21:14.774
Fuck.

21:14.857 --> 21:16.025
[indistinct chatter]

21:16.109 --> 21:17.193
[man] Stay back, buddy.
Stay back.

21:17.276 --> 21:21.572
[Boyd] Shit. Goddamn.

21:21.656 --> 21:23.449
What the--

21:23.533 --> 21:26.536
Okay. Uh...

21:26.619 --> 21:27.996
What do we got here?

21:28.079 --> 21:30.039
-All right.
-Careful. Watch the glass.

21:30.123 --> 21:32.083
Okay. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Hey, sir?

21:32.166 --> 21:33.584
-Hey. Okay.
-[Tabitha] Oh, Jesus.

21:33.668 --> 21:34.836
-Can you hear me? Can you--
-[woman crying]

21:34.919 --> 21:36.254
[Tabitha] Shh, shh, shh.

21:36.337 --> 21:37.547
You're gonna be okay.
You're gonna be okay.

21:37.630 --> 21:38.881
He's got a good strong
pulse, so that's good.

21:38.965 --> 21:40.591
-[Tabitha] You're gonna be okay.
-Okay.

21:40.675 --> 21:41.759
Okay, don't move,
don't move! Don't move!

21:41.843 --> 21:43.428
Please help me.
Help me, please.

21:43.511 --> 21:44.595
[Tabitha]
We're gonna get you out.

21:44.679 --> 21:45.638
-Tabitha?
-[girl] Is he okay?

21:45.722 --> 21:46.889
It's okay.

21:46.973 --> 21:48.099
Is my dad okay?
Is my daddy okay?

21:48.182 --> 21:49.517
Oh, my God.

21:49.600 --> 21:51.102
-Is he-- is my dad okay?
-[Tabitha] Don't move!

21:51.185 --> 21:52.478
You'll be fine.
Don't move your neck!

21:52.562 --> 21:53.479
-Okay.
-Don't move your neck!

21:53.563 --> 21:54.564
[girl] Okay.

21:54.647 --> 21:59.485
[hyperventilating]

21:59.569 --> 22:01.988
Okay. All right, sir, um...

22:02.071 --> 22:03.614
Hey, you know-- hey,

22:03.698 --> 22:05.116
you go to the clinic
and tell them

22:05.199 --> 22:06.659
that we need
the ambulance here right now!

22:06.743 --> 22:08.411
-Yeah, okay.
-Okay?

22:08.494 --> 22:10.997
[grunting with effort]

22:11.080 --> 22:12.665
Okay, do me a favor.

22:12.749 --> 22:14.459
Got a shed on the other side
of the bar. Grab some tools.

22:14.542 --> 22:15.710
We might have to
take this apart, okay?

22:15.793 --> 22:17.003
-You got it.
-[Tabitha] Don't move your neck!

22:17.086 --> 22:18.880
Don't move your neck!
Okay. Relax, breathe.

22:18.963 --> 22:21.049
-What's your name?
-Sophia.

22:21.132 --> 22:22.508
Hey, Sophia, hi.

22:22.592 --> 22:24.302
I'm gonna put
this book in between

22:24.385 --> 22:26.846
your face and this piece of
metal right there, okay?

22:26.929 --> 22:28.139
Okay. Okay.

22:28.222 --> 22:29.432
[Tabitha] Wait. It's okay.

22:29.515 --> 22:30.683
I just wanna make sure
it doesn't cut you

22:30.767 --> 22:31.809
while we get you out, honey.

22:31.893 --> 22:33.186
Okay. Okay.

22:33.269 --> 22:34.395
[gasping]

22:34.479 --> 22:36.230
Okay.

22:36.314 --> 22:38.566
It's gonna be okay.
Just relax. It's gonna be okay.

22:38.649 --> 22:40.359
-[Sophia] Is he gonna okay?
-Yes, he is. Don't move.

22:40.443 --> 22:41.903
Don't move your face,
please, honey.

22:41.986 --> 22:43.112
All right. Is she okay?

22:43.196 --> 22:44.697
[Tabitha]
We need to cut the seatbelt.

22:44.781 --> 22:46.115
Ah, Sophia.

22:46.199 --> 22:47.575
-Did I hear that right?
-[Sophia] Yes!

22:47.658 --> 22:49.285
-[Boyd] Is that your name?
-Yes.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.204
Okay. Sophia, Sophia,
does anything else hurt?

22:51.287 --> 22:52.580
My neck hurts.

22:52.663 --> 22:53.790
Your neck? Okay.
Shh, shh, shh, shh!

22:53.873 --> 22:55.708
Hey, don't--
don't move your neck.

22:55.792 --> 22:57.043
Hey, what about your legs?
What about your legs?

22:57.126 --> 22:58.086
Can you move your toes?

22:58.169 --> 22:59.128
-Move your toes.
-Yeah.

22:59.212 --> 23:00.171
You can?

23:00.254 --> 23:01.547
-Yeah.
-Okay. Okay.

23:01.631 --> 23:02.548
-Okay.
-[Boyd] Don't worry.

23:02.632 --> 23:03.758
-Dad!
-You're gonna be okay.

23:03.841 --> 23:04.759
-You're gonna be fine.
-Your dad's okay.

23:04.842 --> 23:06.052
Dad! Dad!

23:06.135 --> 23:07.512
-[Boyd] Okay. Okay.
-Dad!

23:07.595 --> 23:08.846
Please, wake up!

23:08.930 --> 23:10.848
-[Boyd] Shh...
-[Sophia] Dad, wake up!

23:10.932 --> 23:14.393
Don't move! Don't move
your face, please, honey!

23:14.477 --> 23:16.771
I want my mom! I want my mom!
I don't wanna be here!

23:16.854 --> 23:18.314
-[Boyd] Okay.
-I want my mom!

23:18.397 --> 23:19.565
-[Boyd] Sophia?
-Uh-huh! Yeah?

23:19.649 --> 23:20.775
-Sophia?
-Yeah?

23:20.858 --> 23:21.943
-We're gonna get you, okay?
-Okay.

23:22.026 --> 23:23.236
We just need you
to stay calm, okay?

23:23.319 --> 23:24.737
Okay, but please just
take care of my Dad.

23:24.821 --> 23:25.947
We're gonna take care
of both of you.

23:26.030 --> 23:27.657
-[Tabitha] It's okay.
-It's okay.

23:27.740 --> 23:28.991
Your dad is gonna be fine.

23:29.075 --> 23:30.243
[Boyd] We're gonna help
both of you, okay?

23:30.326 --> 23:31.661
-It's okay. Stay still.
-Okay? Here we go.

23:31.744 --> 23:33.496
[Tabitha] Stay still.
Please don't move.

23:33.579 --> 23:34.497
Just breathe.
We're gonna be out.

23:34.580 --> 23:35.832
[Boyd] Real easy.

23:35.915 --> 23:36.999
It's gonna be okay.
It's gonna be okay.

23:37.083 --> 23:38.501
Just don't move.
It's okay. It's okay.

23:38.584 --> 23:39.752
We're almost there.
Almost done.

23:41.045 --> 23:42.547
-Okay?
-[Boyd] It's okay.

23:46.843 --> 23:48.094
What happened?

23:48.177 --> 23:49.345
Car crash.
We can't get the door open.

23:49.428 --> 23:51.347
There's a driver stuck inside.
Come on.

23:51.430 --> 23:52.390
Pull.

23:52.473 --> 23:54.058
-Okay.
-Dad?!

23:54.142 --> 23:55.768
Okay, no, no, just--
let me put my arms around you.

23:55.852 --> 23:57.228
It's gonna be fine.
It's gonna be fine.

23:57.311 --> 23:59.313
You're gonna be fine.
You're gonna be totally fine.

23:59.397 --> 24:01.149
You're okay.
You're okay.

24:01.232 --> 24:03.151
I'm gonna put my arm around you.
Is that okay? Come on, kiddo.

24:03.234 --> 24:04.861
-Dad!
-[Boyd] He's okay.

24:04.944 --> 24:06.195
Dad! Please!

24:06.279 --> 24:07.572
We'll get him.
We'll get him. Here.

24:07.655 --> 24:08.656
[Tabitha] You're okay.
It's okay, honey.

24:08.739 --> 24:10.366
[Boyd] Stay right there.
You got her?

24:10.449 --> 24:11.742
-Yeah, I've got her.
-Okay, here.

24:11.826 --> 24:13.119
-[Tabitha] It's okay.
-[Boyd] Take her.

24:13.202 --> 24:14.370
It's okay.

24:14.453 --> 24:15.872
[Sophia gasping]

24:19.000 --> 24:22.587
[breathing heavily]

24:22.670 --> 24:25.089
[engine revving]

24:26.591 --> 24:29.093
Get back. Get back.

24:29.177 --> 24:30.261
Hey! Stop.

24:33.181 --> 24:34.932
Great.
Hey, did you grab the gurney?

24:35.016 --> 24:36.642
Look, we just
pulled the daughter out.

24:36.726 --> 24:37.810
The dad is still inside.

24:37.894 --> 24:39.103
He's breathing,
got a good pulse.

24:39.187 --> 24:40.229
-Is he talking?
-No, no.

24:49.197 --> 24:50.156
Perfect.

24:53.993 --> 24:56.454
[woman] Out of the way.
Let us through!

24:56.537 --> 24:58.456
[Tabitha] Here we go.
Here we go.

24:58.539 --> 25:00.166
You're okay.

25:26.400 --> 25:28.527
Hey, you're okay. We're gonna
take care of your father, okay?

25:28.611 --> 25:29.862
-Hey.
-It's gonna be okay. Hey.

25:29.946 --> 25:31.864
Hi.

25:31.948 --> 25:33.824
-It's Sophia, right?
-Yes, ma'am.

25:33.908 --> 25:35.034
Okay. My name's Marielle.

25:35.117 --> 25:37.662
-Are you a doctor?
-I'm a nurse.

25:37.745 --> 25:39.413
Okay.

25:39.497 --> 25:41.666
-She has it right here too.
-Mm-hmm.

25:44.752 --> 25:45.878
Got it.

25:45.962 --> 25:48.297
Okay, perfect. Yeah.

25:48.381 --> 25:50.591
[grunts]

25:50.675 --> 25:53.094
Okay, can you tell me
anything about the accident?

25:53.177 --> 25:56.013
Was your dad
acting strange at all?

25:56.097 --> 25:57.056
Did he say anything?

25:57.139 --> 25:59.141
He-- he was. Um...

25:59.225 --> 26:02.186
There was, um--
there was a tree on the road

26:02.270 --> 26:04.814
and we were trying
to find a way around it

26:04.897 --> 26:06.565
to get back on the highway,

26:06.649 --> 26:09.652
and then he-- he just--

26:09.735 --> 26:12.280
he made a sound, and then
he just started shaking,

26:12.363 --> 26:14.991
and then we started
going faster, and then--

26:15.074 --> 26:16.993
You're doing good.
You're doing good.

26:17.076 --> 26:18.327
It's okay. It's okay.

26:18.411 --> 26:21.330
I, um...
I-I tried to steer the car,

26:21.414 --> 26:23.916
but he was just moving
so much and thrashing

26:24.000 --> 26:27.044
that I-- I couldn't--
and then we just--and then we--

26:27.128 --> 26:29.297
Okay. You're good.
It's okay. It's okay.

26:29.380 --> 26:32.216
Please, please don't
let my daddy die.

26:32.300 --> 26:33.718
No, no, no. It's okay.

26:33.801 --> 26:35.219
I'm gonna give you a second.

26:35.303 --> 26:37.388
Please don't let my daddy die.
I don't want him to die.

26:37.471 --> 26:39.640
It's okay.
You need to breathe. It's okay.

26:39.724 --> 26:42.059
We're gonna take care of him.
We're gonna take care of him.

26:42.143 --> 26:43.436
[grunts]

26:44.895 --> 26:48.107
[straining]

26:48.190 --> 26:49.233
You guys should use a winch.

26:49.317 --> 26:51.319
Ethan, stay with Victor.

26:51.402 --> 26:52.778
-Huh?
-What?

26:52.862 --> 26:54.071
-A winch.
-[Julie] Can I help?

26:54.155 --> 26:56.741
-[Boyd] Bring it.
-Grab that shit.

27:00.870 --> 27:01.495
Here.

27:03.122 --> 27:04.081
Watch your hands.

27:07.001 --> 27:09.462
[Jade] Okay, uh, tie this up.

27:09.545 --> 27:11.756
[Boyd] Make sure it's tight.
Get the ra-- rachet.

27:11.839 --> 27:12.965
[Kenny] Okay, I'm gonna grab
the gurney.

27:14.675 --> 27:16.344
Let's go! Let's go!

27:19.013 --> 27:20.556
Yep. We'll take it.
We'll take it.

27:20.639 --> 27:21.807
Wait...
Wait for me.

27:21.891 --> 27:23.601
All right. Right.
Just-- get the seatbelt.

27:23.684 --> 27:24.810
Yeah, I got it.

27:28.022 --> 27:29.023
[Boyd] Okay.
You got him?

27:29.106 --> 27:31.192
Okay, get that on him.

27:31.275 --> 27:32.318
[Kenny]
Yup.

27:32.401 --> 27:33.819
[grunting]

27:33.903 --> 27:35.780
-Right here.
-[Kenny] Careful.

27:35.863 --> 27:37.198
-You got him?
-[Jade] Yeah.

27:37.281 --> 27:39.033
[Kenny] We good?

27:40.159 --> 27:41.035
[Boyd] One, two, three.

27:41.118 --> 27:42.745
[grunts]

27:42.828 --> 27:43.788
[Boyd] All right.

27:43.871 --> 27:45.081
-Good?
-[Kenny] Yeah.

27:45.164 --> 27:46.207
-[Boyd] Let's get it.
-[Kenny] I got it.

27:47.291 --> 27:48.209
[Randall] Okay.

27:48.292 --> 27:49.502
[Boyd] Yeah. You got it?

27:49.585 --> 27:50.795
All right.

27:50.878 --> 27:52.171
Hey.

27:52.254 --> 27:53.881
-From what his daughter says...
-Right.

27:53.964 --> 27:55.716
...I think he had a seizure.

27:55.800 --> 27:58.010
I'm not sure what's wrong
with him is actually medical.

27:58.844 --> 28:00.012
What are you talking about?

28:00.096 --> 28:01.639
The day I got here,
I watched Elgin

28:01.722 --> 28:03.349
have an unprovoked seizure
right over there.

28:03.432 --> 28:04.600
But, based on what
I've been told,

28:04.683 --> 28:06.018
that's not entirely uncommon?

28:06.102 --> 28:07.436
Oh, right, yeah.

28:07.520 --> 28:08.938
Ethan had one the first night
he was here

28:09.021 --> 28:10.147
and Sara had one in the diner.

28:10.231 --> 28:12.691
-[Marielle] Right.
-Wasn't like this.

28:12.775 --> 28:14.276
So, what do we do?

28:14.360 --> 28:16.028
[Marielle]
I mean, at this point,

28:16.112 --> 28:17.738
bring him back up to the clinic
and hope he wakes up.

28:18.989 --> 28:20.408
Okay.

28:20.491 --> 28:23.119
Hey. I'm gonna stay up
at the clinic tonight.

28:23.202 --> 28:24.453
Wha-- Are you sure?

28:24.537 --> 28:26.163
Yeah.
It's gonna be a tough night,

28:26.247 --> 28:28.374
and one of us should be
up there with them,

28:28.457 --> 28:32.002
and you need to go
see Fatima and Ellis.

28:32.086 --> 28:33.712
-Right. Okay.
-Yeah.

28:33.796 --> 28:35.089
Okay, yeah.

28:35.172 --> 28:36.590
-All right.
-All right. I got the door.

28:36.674 --> 28:38.092
-Okay.
-[Boyd] You okay?

28:41.637 --> 28:44.723
[engine starts]

28:52.481 --> 28:54.275
Where do you think
they're gonna live?

28:55.401 --> 28:58.362
We'll have to wait and see.

28:58.446 --> 29:01.740
Let's go home.
It's gonna be dark soon.

29:01.824 --> 29:03.284
Where's Dad?

29:04.952 --> 29:06.537
I don't know, but he'll
be here before dark.

29:06.620 --> 29:08.497
Let's go. Let's go. Come on.

29:08.581 --> 29:10.082
Come on.
Let's go. It's okay.

29:10.166 --> 29:11.500
Hope they're okay.

29:11.584 --> 29:12.460
[Jade] Tabitha.

29:13.586 --> 29:14.503
Jade.

29:15.671 --> 29:16.630
We need to talk.

29:19.800 --> 29:21.802
It's okay. Go.
Get inside.

29:21.886 --> 29:23.012
We need to tell people.

29:23.095 --> 29:24.263
Tell them what?

29:24.346 --> 29:26.599
We have no idea
what happened out there.

29:26.682 --> 29:27.850
We don't even know
if it's true.

29:27.933 --> 29:29.185
You're gonna stand there
and you're gonna tell me

29:29.268 --> 29:30.186
that didn't feel real to you?

29:30.269 --> 29:31.562
I don't know what I feel.

29:33.939 --> 29:35.524
Sara tried to kill my son

29:35.608 --> 29:37.568
because something out here
convinced her

29:37.651 --> 29:39.612
that if she did that,
we could all go home.

29:40.446 --> 29:41.906
I'm sure that
felt very real to her.

29:41.989 --> 29:43.240
No, no, no.
Hey, wait, wait.

29:43.324 --> 29:44.283
Listen, that was different.

29:44.366 --> 29:45.534
How?

29:45.618 --> 29:46.785
Uh...

29:46.869 --> 29:48.913
What's easier to believe -

29:48.996 --> 29:50.623
that whatever is keeping
us here

29:50.706 --> 29:53.000
put those thoughts
in our heads to torture us,

29:53.083 --> 29:54.585
or...

29:54.668 --> 29:58.088
that you and I have
been coming back here

29:58.172 --> 30:01.717
over and over again,
for centuries,

30:01.800 --> 30:06.722
trying to save children
that are already dead? I mean...

30:06.805 --> 30:09.308
Listen. We can-- We can go
inside, okay?

30:09.391 --> 30:11.060
You, me, Jim,
we can pull this--

30:11.143 --> 30:14.271
Jim's not here.
Jim's not home.

30:14.355 --> 30:15.689
What are you talking about?
It's almost dark.

30:15.773 --> 30:17.274
I know. I know.

30:17.358 --> 30:21.320
When he's back,
I'll talk to him.

30:21.403 --> 30:22.488
Okay.

30:24.615 --> 30:25.824
Okay.

30:30.829 --> 30:34.250
Hey, we need to talk
about what happened earlier.

30:35.251 --> 30:37.711
-Give me a minute--
-Get your fucking hands off me!

30:37.795 --> 30:41.131
Look, it is getting dark.

30:41.215 --> 30:42.550
You can't just be
walking around out here.

30:42.633 --> 30:43.884
Yeah, I'm not going back
in there with you,

30:43.968 --> 30:44.885
that's for goddamn--

30:44.969 --> 30:46.637
I know, I know, I know.

30:46.720 --> 30:47.972
You don't know shit.

30:49.306 --> 30:51.517
You think you're
some kind of hero?

30:51.600 --> 30:54.812
You're some martyr
who did what you had to do?

30:54.895 --> 30:57.856
What you did to
that kid up there...

30:57.940 --> 30:59.858
You're a fucking monster.

31:02.444 --> 31:05.573
I don't know what
you were before,

31:05.656 --> 31:06.907
but that is what you are now.

31:08.993 --> 31:10.828
All you people
are fucking monsters.

31:18.544 --> 31:19.420
[door opens]

31:21.422 --> 31:24.341
Sun's about to go down.
You spending the night?

31:24.425 --> 31:26.051
If that's okay.

31:26.135 --> 31:31.015
Yeah. Uh, Kristi's
upstairs with Fatima now.

31:31.098 --> 31:33.726
She just finished
stitching up Elgin's eye.

31:33.809 --> 31:34.977
Right.

31:35.060 --> 31:36.604
Um...

31:36.687 --> 31:39.023
We need to talk about
what we're doing with him.

31:40.983 --> 31:42.526
Boyd?

31:42.610 --> 31:43.902
Yeah. Yeah.

31:43.986 --> 31:45.571
Yeah. I, uh...

31:47.364 --> 31:49.867
You should come upstairs
with me.

31:49.950 --> 31:51.827
There's something
you need to hear.

32:38.874 --> 32:40.292
[exhaling sharply]

32:40.376 --> 32:42.211
["Send in the Clowns"
by Frank Sinatra plays]

32:42.294 --> 32:44.630
♪ Isn't it rich? ♪

32:46.632 --> 32:49.635
♪ Are we a pair? ♪

32:52.054 --> 32:53.514
♪ Me here at last ♪

32:53.597 --> 32:55.599
-[metallic slamming]
-♪ On the ground ♪

32:55.683 --> 32:59.019
♪ You in mid-air ♪

33:00.771 --> 33:03.774
♪ Send in the clowns ♪

33:03.857 --> 33:07.319
[breathing rapidly]

33:09.905 --> 33:12.157
[breathing heavily]

33:12.241 --> 33:14.827
♪ Isn't it bliss? ♪

33:17.371 --> 33:18.539
♪ Don't you-- ♪

33:20.457 --> 33:21.959
[Kristi] Okay.

33:22.042 --> 33:24.920
We're all done.
You did great.

33:26.046 --> 33:27.256
Am I okay?

33:27.339 --> 33:28.966
Physically,

33:29.049 --> 33:31.343
everything looks fine.

33:36.014 --> 33:39.935
Is there anything you
can tell me about the... um...

33:41.562 --> 33:42.688
the--

33:42.771 --> 33:45.274
-The birth?
-Yeah.

33:45.357 --> 33:47.568
What would you like to know?

33:48.736 --> 33:52.197
About the terrifying woman in
the kimono that held me down

33:52.281 --> 33:53.741
or the thing
she pulled out of me

33:53.824 --> 33:55.534
that you told me wasn't there?

33:58.328 --> 34:00.080
[knocking]

34:00.164 --> 34:01.123
[Boyd] Boyd.

34:01.206 --> 34:02.207
Come in.

34:06.545 --> 34:07.463
Hey.

34:08.880 --> 34:10.174
How you doing?

34:10.257 --> 34:11.884
[Fatima] What did you see
in the tunnels?

34:11.967 --> 34:13.927
Did you find
the woman in the kimono?

34:14.011 --> 34:15.721
I did.

34:15.804 --> 34:18.264
-I'm gonna head out.
-No, stay. Stay.

34:18.348 --> 34:19.641
You should, um...

34:23.020 --> 34:24.271
You, uh...

34:25.898 --> 34:27.440
You should hear this.

34:29.150 --> 34:30.027
-Okay.
-Okay.

34:31.320 --> 34:32.946
-Dad?
-Yeah.

34:33.030 --> 34:35.783
What's going on?
What happened down there?

34:37.451 --> 34:39.828
So, uh...

34:39.911 --> 34:41.996
by the time
I caught up to her, the, uh,

34:42.080 --> 34:45.751
uh... the woman
with the kimono, uh,

34:45.833 --> 34:48.504
she was in
a chamber with those--

34:48.587 --> 34:50.505
those things from the woods,
and they--

34:50.589 --> 34:52.882
they were all
standing around in a circle.

34:52.966 --> 34:56.594
Um, and she, um--

34:56.678 --> 34:57.846
she was holding the...

35:00.808 --> 35:04.478
She put it in the center
of the-- of the room,

35:04.561 --> 35:05.521
and, um...

35:05.604 --> 35:07.606
it started to move.

35:10.317 --> 35:11.944
And then it started to grow.

35:13.987 --> 35:18.075
And it-- it kept... growing

35:18.158 --> 35:21.829
until it got big enough...

35:21.912 --> 35:22.955
to stand.

35:24.623 --> 35:26.208
And then, it smiled.

35:28.126 --> 35:31.088
I gave birth to one of them.

35:31.171 --> 35:33.006
[Ellis] No.
That's not what he's saying.

35:33.090 --> 35:34.091
Dad, tell her that's--
that's--

35:34.174 --> 35:35.175
that's not what you're saying.

35:35.259 --> 35:36.844
[gasping]

35:36.927 --> 35:38.971
This is not just one of them.

35:40.055 --> 35:41.557
It's the one I killed...

35:43.392 --> 35:44.726
that night at the clinic.

35:44.810 --> 35:45.686
Jesus.

35:47.354 --> 35:50.524
[rumbling]

35:52.651 --> 35:54.444
[Victor straining]

35:54.528 --> 35:56.864
Victor?
Victor!

35:56.947 --> 35:57.865
[breathing heavily]

35:57.948 --> 36:00.158
What are you doing?

36:00.242 --> 36:02.369
I'm dragging
this bed into my room.

36:02.452 --> 36:04.580
I can see that.
You wanna tell me why?

36:04.663 --> 36:06.623
It's-- well, it's for my dad.

36:06.707 --> 36:09.918
Uh, we're gonna
be roommates now.

36:10.002 --> 36:12.754
Um, here, let me help with that.
Sorry about the noise.

36:12.838 --> 36:14.298
It's okay.

36:15.132 --> 36:17.175
It's been a while
since I've had a roommate.

36:17.259 --> 36:19.887
-I'm sure you'll figure it out.
-Yeah.

36:20.929 --> 36:23.473
[Boyd]
Look. Listen. Look at me. Now--

36:25.434 --> 36:28.312
Boyd, are you sure
it was the same one?

36:30.230 --> 36:31.732
Yeah.

36:31.815 --> 36:33.650
Look, if Kenny
hadn't been there,

36:33.734 --> 36:35.360
if he hadn't
seen it as well,

36:35.444 --> 36:36.778
I'd have thought
I'd lost my mind.

36:36.862 --> 36:39.573
But he said you
said something after,

36:39.656 --> 36:40.866
something important.

36:40.949 --> 36:42.576
I-I sa--

36:42.659 --> 36:44.703
About something promising them
that they'd live forever.

36:44.786 --> 36:47.080
It was just a glimpse, but...

36:47.164 --> 36:49.708
[breathing heavily]
...I saw what they did.

36:49.791 --> 36:50.834
Okay.

36:50.918 --> 36:54.588
Those things in the woods,

36:54.671 --> 36:56.882
I think I saw how they
became what they are.

36:58.842 --> 37:02.137
They made a bargain

37:02.220 --> 37:06.892
because something promised them
that they would live...

37:06.975 --> 37:08.310
forever.

37:09.811 --> 37:12.105
A bargain.
With-- With what?

37:13.357 --> 37:14.399
I don't-- I don't know.

37:14.483 --> 37:15.359
Fatima...

37:17.319 --> 37:19.613
I don't-- what-- I don't know!
I-I couldn't see it.

37:19.696 --> 37:20.948
Look, look.
Listen, listen, listen to me.

37:21.031 --> 37:22.950
I know that you
have been through a lot,

37:23.033 --> 37:24.743
but this is important.

37:24.826 --> 37:28.538
[gasps]
You think I don't know that?

37:28.622 --> 37:29.957
I'm not--

37:30.040 --> 37:31.416
I'm the one that...

37:32.876 --> 37:34.378
[breathing unsteadily]

37:34.461 --> 37:35.796
-I need a shower.
-Hey, whoa. Hey, easy.

37:35.879 --> 37:37.255
-I need a fucking shower.
-Baby, no. You need rest.

37:37.339 --> 37:38.715
-Fatima, hold on.
-Fatima, don't.

37:38.799 --> 37:41.134
-You just need to rest--
-[Fatima] No! I need a shower!

37:41.218 --> 37:44.471
[breathing shakily]

37:44.554 --> 37:47.349
I told you!

37:47.432 --> 37:49.851
I told all of you

37:49.935 --> 37:52.604
that there was something
inside me,

37:52.688 --> 37:54.231
something that...

37:57.901 --> 38:00.404
I begged you to listen!

38:02.406 --> 38:05.158
I don't--
I don't understand what I saw.

38:05.242 --> 38:08.412
I don't know why I saw it.
I didn't--

38:08.495 --> 38:10.455
There's nothing else
I can tell you.

38:11.623 --> 38:13.125
Okay.

38:13.208 --> 38:14.292
I'm sorry.

38:14.376 --> 38:15.335
I'm sorry.

38:15.419 --> 38:17.504
Hey, it's...

38:29.516 --> 38:30.934
Be honest,

38:31.018 --> 38:34.813
what do you think
the chances are he wakes up?

38:36.314 --> 38:40.902
Uh, given how long
he's been out for?

38:42.404 --> 38:43.697
It's not even
so much if he wakes up,

38:43.780 --> 38:45.407
but what kind of shape
he'll be in if he does.

38:45.490 --> 38:46.408
Yeah.

38:50.412 --> 38:52.164
-Kenny?
-Yeah.

38:52.247 --> 38:55.500
Do you have a phone? I, um--
I left mine in the car, and I--

38:55.584 --> 38:57.794
I-I need to call my mom.
She's probably worried sick.

38:58.920 --> 39:01.381
Yeah, um, there's, uh...

39:01.465 --> 39:05.635
There's no...
There's no cell service here.

39:05.719 --> 39:07.054
I could just
go down the hill. It's okay.

39:07.137 --> 39:09.264
I-I don't mean...

39:09.347 --> 39:11.808
I don't mean
here in the clinic.

39:11.892 --> 39:13.185
[Marielle]
I'm gonna go.

39:14.686 --> 39:15.687
I, uh...

39:15.771 --> 39:17.606
What's going on?

39:17.689 --> 39:19.900
I-I need to call my mom.

39:19.983 --> 39:24.279
I know. I understand. I do.

39:24.362 --> 39:28.366
I... I wish I could, um...

39:29.785 --> 39:34.414
We need to have a talk...
about this place

39:34.498 --> 39:37.459
and about that tree
that you saw in the road.

39:46.468 --> 39:47.677
[Julie] Mom.

39:48.804 --> 39:50.931
Where is he?

39:51.014 --> 39:52.849
Why isn't he back yet?

39:52.933 --> 39:54.768
Honey,
your father's fine.

39:54.851 --> 39:56.895
It's not like he's late
coming home from work.

39:56.978 --> 40:00.440
Mom, what happened today?
Why won't you talk to me?

40:00.524 --> 40:02.025
No, Julie, no.
I-I don't wanna talk right now.

40:02.109 --> 40:03.693
-Please!
-I can't.

40:03.777 --> 40:05.153
-Please!
-I can't talk to you.

40:05.237 --> 40:06.738
-I can't talk to you now.
-Stop saying that! Please!

40:06.822 --> 40:09.950
Mom, it's almost dark.
He's not home.

40:10.033 --> 40:11.243
Please, why won't you talk--

40:11.326 --> 40:14.746
[Ethan] Stop it.
Stop yelling at each other.

40:15.956 --> 40:19.167
No, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

40:20.085 --> 40:21.211
-[door closes]
-Is Dad dead?

40:22.754 --> 40:24.089
No!

40:25.507 --> 40:26.800
No, honey. No, he's not.

40:29.344 --> 40:31.805
Maybe he didn't realize
how late it was.

40:31.888 --> 40:33.390
I don't know.

40:33.473 --> 40:38.186
Maybe he's at the Colony House
or the RV.

40:38.270 --> 40:40.147
We'll see him tomorrow.

40:40.230 --> 40:41.940
Well, what if we don't?

40:44.025 --> 40:45.235
Well...

40:45.318 --> 40:46.736
Do you remember
what Dad said to us,

40:46.820 --> 40:48.155
the night that Mom
went to the Bottle Tree

40:48.238 --> 40:49.698
and didn't come home?

40:50.907 --> 40:53.535
He said all we have in this
place is what we believe.

40:53.618 --> 40:56.204
So, we have to
believe good things.

40:56.288 --> 40:57.164
Right?

40:59.082 --> 41:00.834
Mom came home.

41:02.377 --> 41:03.587
Dad will, too.

41:09.134 --> 41:13.722
So, um, the monsters, they--
they come every night?

41:13.805 --> 41:15.098
Yeah.

41:15.182 --> 41:19.144
These-- These rocks,
they-- they protect you?

41:19.227 --> 41:21.062
Uh, we call them talismans.

41:21.146 --> 41:22.689
How do they work?

41:22.772 --> 41:25.483
Don't! Don't, um...

41:25.567 --> 41:27.694
Don't take it off the window.

41:27.777 --> 41:29.154
Sorry.

41:29.237 --> 41:31.573
It's okay. It's just, um...

41:31.656 --> 41:34.117
they have to be
hanging for it to work.

41:34.201 --> 41:35.285
Why?

41:38.288 --> 41:39.873
[exhaling sharply]
Uh...

41:39.956 --> 41:42.626
We-- We don't know.

41:42.709 --> 41:43.960
We don't know.

41:44.044 --> 41:47.005
I know how
this must all sound.

41:47.088 --> 41:48.506
"The light shines
in the darkness,

41:48.590 --> 41:50.175
"and the darkness
shall not overcome it."

41:50.258 --> 41:51.885
What is that?

41:51.968 --> 41:53.386
John 1:5.

41:53.470 --> 41:55.680
It means that,
um, God is with us,

41:55.764 --> 41:57.807
even here.

41:57.891 --> 42:01.561
I mean, um, how else can you
explain such a magical thing

42:01.645 --> 42:03.230
to keep the darkness at bay?

42:05.232 --> 42:06.358
Right.

42:06.441 --> 42:08.360
Will you pray
with me, Kenny?

42:09.736 --> 42:11.196
Oh, I'm not--

42:11.279 --> 42:13.156
I'm not really, uh...

42:13.240 --> 42:14.950
I'm not really religious.

42:15.033 --> 42:17.202
That's okay.
God still listens.

42:18.662 --> 42:19.704
Please?

42:22.415 --> 42:24.542
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

42:28.880 --> 42:29.756
[exhaling sharply]

42:31.424 --> 42:34.094
Lord, please protect us
in this dark place,

42:34.177 --> 42:37.347
where evil roams so freely.

42:37.430 --> 42:39.015
Please stand by
my daddy's bedside

42:39.099 --> 42:41.643
and let him wake
renewed in Your love.

42:41.726 --> 42:44.271
And please rest Your hand upon
the shoulders of these people,

42:44.354 --> 42:46.314
trapped here in this place,
who have taken us in

42:46.398 --> 42:48.900
and shown us such kindness.

42:48.984 --> 42:50.402
Be with them tonight,
O Lord,

42:50.485 --> 42:52.779
and let Your love
give them rest.

42:52.862 --> 42:55.448
This we ask in Your name.
Amen.

42:58.660 --> 43:00.120
Uh, Amen.

43:02.455 --> 43:05.250
Um, I'm gonna go sit with
my daddy now, if that's okay.

43:05.333 --> 43:07.377
Yeah. Of course.

43:51.129 --> 43:52.756
There are a lot of people
wanting to know

43:52.839 --> 43:54.674
what happened down there.

43:56.092 --> 43:57.802
Boyd?

43:57.886 --> 43:59.471
You hear what I said?

43:59.554 --> 44:01.264
We had another car today.

44:03.308 --> 44:05.143
A girl and her dad.

44:06.061 --> 44:09.147
Looked like a...
like a pastor, maybe.

44:11.274 --> 44:13.485
He had a--
he had a stroke...

44:14.736 --> 44:17.572
...or a seizure or something.

44:17.655 --> 44:22.202
They crashed into
the Sheriff's Station.

44:22.285 --> 44:24.913
The girl can't be
more than I don't know, 15,

44:24.996 --> 44:27.457
16 years old. She's, uh...

44:27.540 --> 44:29.376
She's up
at the clinic right now,

44:29.459 --> 44:31.586
waiting to see if her dad
lives through the night,

44:31.669 --> 44:33.088
while Kenny explains to her

44:33.171 --> 44:37.217
that whatever life
she had before...

44:37.300 --> 44:38.468
is over,

44:38.551 --> 44:40.428
that, now,
she lives in a place

44:40.512 --> 44:43.473
where monsters smile.

44:46.518 --> 44:48.436
That girl's probably
gonna die here.

44:48.520 --> 44:50.480
-Boyd!
-You know,

44:50.563 --> 44:53.942
the only thing that gets me
out of bed in the morning

44:54.025 --> 44:57.237
is the idea that...

44:57.320 --> 45:01.324
maybe, just-- just maybe,
we can beat this place,

45:01.408 --> 45:04.536
that maybe we can get
everybody home,

45:04.619 --> 45:06.704
that, someday, maybe

45:06.788 --> 45:11.209
the good guys actually win!

45:11.292 --> 45:14.379
And then I saw that
fucking thing in the tunnels!

45:14.462 --> 45:17.632
The same goddamn smile--
that same...

45:17.715 --> 45:19.509
And I realized--

45:19.592 --> 45:22.137
I mean, this place has been
three steps ahead of us

45:22.220 --> 45:23.638
from the beginning!

45:23.721 --> 45:25.598
Just like you said,
the game's rigged.

45:25.682 --> 45:27.475
Doesn't matter what we do.

45:27.559 --> 45:29.644
Doesn't matter
what we sacrifice.

45:29.727 --> 45:33.898
None of it means
a goddamn thing if we can't--

45:33.982 --> 45:35.066
Hey, where you going?

45:35.150 --> 45:37.735
I am not going anywhere.

45:37.819 --> 45:40.155
None of us are.

45:40.238 --> 45:41.948
Okay, no, fuck this.

45:42.031 --> 45:43.741
Get out of my way, Kristi!

45:43.825 --> 45:45.743
No, no.
You don't get to do this.

45:45.827 --> 45:47.495
It's a pretty
shit time for you

45:47.579 --> 45:48.538
to start feeling sorry
for yourself.

45:48.621 --> 45:49.956
Oh, is that what I'm doing?

45:50.039 --> 45:51.624
Yeah, you are!

45:51.708 --> 45:53.751
And you have plenty
of reasons to.

45:53.835 --> 45:56.921
So does everybody else here.
But none of those people

45:57.005 --> 45:59.340
are asking me to stitch up
people's eye sockets,

45:59.424 --> 46:01.468
so I'm gonna need
a little more from you

46:01.551 --> 46:02.927
than "These monsters
live forever,

46:03.011 --> 46:05.180
"so we're all gonna die."

46:05.263 --> 46:06.848
Because it doesn't matter
how many people

46:06.931 --> 46:08.308
I stitch back up together,

46:08.391 --> 46:10.226
if they see you lose faith,

46:10.310 --> 46:11.978
then that's
when people start

46:12.061 --> 46:13.438
hanging themselves
in the bathroom.

46:14.981 --> 46:17.192
Can you guys
give us a second?

46:18.359 --> 46:19.486
Yeah.

46:19.569 --> 46:21.488
[Donna] Let's go.

46:21.571 --> 46:23.198
[clears throat]

46:23.281 --> 46:24.282
Let's go.

46:41.341 --> 46:43.218
Kristi's right, Dad.

46:44.886 --> 46:47.514
Look, no matter what happens,

46:47.597 --> 46:51.267
you are the one person
that nobody here can see...

46:53.978 --> 46:56.481
-Dad!
-I can't do it anymore.

46:56.564 --> 46:58.942
Ellis, I can't!

46:59.025 --> 47:00.443
I'm falling apart!

47:03.780 --> 47:08.618
Everything I've done,
every sacrifice we've made,

47:08.701 --> 47:11.663
and if--
if I can't get you home,

47:11.746 --> 47:14.207
then none of it matters!
Your mom?!

47:14.290 --> 47:15.833
Your mom?!

47:15.917 --> 47:16.793
It's...

47:18.419 --> 47:20.088
Fuck,
it can't be for nothing!

47:20.171 --> 47:21.506
I just-- I...

47:21.589 --> 47:24.884
[voice breaking]
I can't fucking...

47:24.968 --> 47:28.221
I cannot...

47:28.304 --> 47:30.223
any...

47:30.306 --> 47:31.307
God.

47:31.391 --> 47:36.312
[sobbing]

47:36.396 --> 47:38.022
[Ellis] I know.

47:39.649 --> 47:40.692
I know.

47:40.775 --> 47:42.819
[sobbing]

47:54.414 --> 47:57.083
[metallic clattering]

47:58.501 --> 48:00.920
What was that?

48:01.004 --> 48:02.171
I don't know.

48:04.507 --> 48:04.799
Mom?

48:07.844 --> 48:11.764
[suspenseful music]

48:40.627 --> 48:46.341
♪

48:46.424 --> 48:47.425
What's happening?

49:37.725 --> 49:41.979
[breathing deeply]

49:46.192 --> 49:47.235
Wake up.

49:53.282 --> 49:54.534
That's better.

49:56.327 --> 49:58.538
Blink twice
if you can hear me.

50:01.457 --> 50:04.127
I know this must be
very confusing for you.

50:04.210 --> 50:06.921
But it's important
you understand

50:07.004 --> 50:11.968
that you played a very special
role in a very important story.

50:21.769 --> 50:24.689
You see, um...

50:24.772 --> 50:27.233
I couldn't've come
to them as I was.

50:31.612 --> 50:34.991
[exhales, laughs]

50:35.074 --> 50:37.785
[Sophia] Not with everything
they learned.

50:45.918 --> 50:49.464
[groaning]

50:49.547 --> 50:53.885
[groaning continues]

50:55.678 --> 50:58.014
-[groaning]
-[cracking]

50:58.097 --> 51:01.100
[groaning]

51:01.184 --> 51:02.852
[bones cracking]

51:02.935 --> 51:04.937
[groaning]

51:05.021 --> 51:08.858
[bones cracking]

51:08.941 --> 51:10.318
[groaning]

51:10.401 --> 51:13.863
[feminine groaning]

51:13.946 --> 51:17.492
[bones cracking]

51:30.546 --> 51:32.965
What's happening
to you isn't fair.

51:44.560 --> 51:45.686
Are you all right?

51:45.770 --> 51:47.104
I'm lost.

51:47.188 --> 51:48.481
Me too.

51:49.565 --> 51:51.317
Would you like a ride?

51:54.320 --> 51:56.072
When you stopped for me,

51:56.155 --> 51:58.282
I know you did so
with kindness in your heart.

52:04.247 --> 52:05.248
[gasps]

52:08.376 --> 52:10.044
[engine revving]

52:11.337 --> 52:12.755
[engine revving]

52:12.839 --> 52:14.298
[tires screeching]

52:16.050 --> 52:19.512
You must be so afraid.

52:19.595 --> 52:22.390
I'm sorry you won't be here
to see what comes next.

52:23.641 --> 52:25.601
It's always
my favorite part.

52:28.104 --> 52:30.690
It's the part I wish
could last forever.

52:32.441 --> 52:33.818
Would you like to know why?

52:39.907 --> 52:43.119
This is when
they tear themselves apart.

52:46.455 --> 52:48.374
[muffled grunting]

52:48.457 --> 52:50.459
[grunting continues]

52:57.800 --> 53:04.682
♪
